WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. -- Wake Forest is taking on North Carolina this Saturday in Chapel Hill. The Tar Heels have an explosive offense and are expected to be a big challenge for the Demon Deacons. 
Before we look ahead, lets look back: 
The Demon Deacons got their first A-C-C win of the season last week at Boston College. They did it without scoring a single touchdown. This image says it all: 
The pile is one place. The ball is not in that place 
These 10 Things: Wake Forest, Boston College brings us to a low point 
Wake beat BC 3-0 and it was ugly down to the final seconds. 
Last season, Virginia Tech head coach, Frank Beamer looked jubilant when regulation against Wake ended scoreless. The final score in that one was 6-3. The Deacs won in the worst double overtime game we've seen in a while. 
I know, a win is a win, and Wake fans will take it. If you can beat a team without finding the endzone, more power to you. Read or Share this story: http://on.wfmy.com/1RL4wMh TOP VIDEOS
